“Ruth’s songs are a true wonder. Her voice bathes over meas if I have soaked myself in a healing sound-shower.”Steve Lee, Glastonbury FM
Beloved Ones,The time has finally come around to ask you to come on board with this project: my new album 'Creation'. Thank you for being here. The jist of this crowdfunder is - I'm making an album, I'm on the final leg of the journey and I need your help to make it happen. I have some beautiful gifts to offer in exchange. I hope you will dive in and find some treasures that will excite and inspire you, and most of all I hope that together we can make this happen and bring this new wave of healing into the world. Outlined below is what I'm doing, what I'm asking, what I'm offering, and the story of it all. The BackgroundIt seems like a lifetime ago that I asked you to join me on my maiden voyage - my debut album, 'Lullabies for Grown-Ups' - an album of songs straight from my heart that I still turn to when I need to receive the medicine they bring. I remember how much fear and self-doubt I had about running a crowdfunder back the and the support I received blew my socks off! All those that supported me then, I thank you again now! And all those who are newly joining me - hello! I'm so thrilled and delighted and all manner of lovely words to be connecting to an ever greater web of beautiful hearts. I welcome you into my life, and I thank you for considering to join me on this journey.The new album is a totally different flavour to my 'Lullabies...', and its journey into being has been bigger, longer and more adventurous. I promised myself from the beginning that I would give it time and space to breathe and not limit myself with fears of lack, and as a result I feel my creativity has been allowed to blossom.The album naturally became a creative collaboration of artists, all of whom I wish to honour for their incredible work, which is why I have included a fee for them in my funding goal. Francesca Booth and Chloe Purcell have given months and months of their time, commitment and inspiration  to create unique offerings of artwork and animation that form part of the wider vision for enriching, celebrating and promoting the album. What I'm asking forRecording, releasing and promoting an album is a big undertaking, and expensive for an unsigned artist without the support of a record label. This epic nature of this collaborative project is reflected in the amount I am now looking to raise - £12,000. It is not easy to estimate some of the costs in advance but the rough breakdown is:Recording & Mixing - £4000Mastering - £600CD Duplication - £1500Artwork & Sleeve Design - £1000Print & Framing costs - £900Web Support (Ongoing) - £400Launch Party - £1000Music Video - £1000Miscellaneous Expenses - £500Indie Gogo Fees - £600 - £1100 (5-9% depending if goal is met)*Any extra money raised will go towards promotion such as a radio campaign.If finances are difficult for you but you still want to offer your support, the best way is to share, share, share! Share the campaign, my brand new Patreon site, Soundcloud, You Tube, Spotify and website links. Let people know about your relationship with my music and invite them to join in, listen and share it themselves... If you have skills that you feel may help me in marketing or promotion, or if you are able to write blogs, reviews or articles to promote me and the new album, then please please get in touch. This can be invaluable support and I am happy to offer tailor-made exchanges for your time. What I'm OfferingPlease enjoy looking through the 'perks' I have lovingly put together to show my gratitude for your offerings towards this album:
Be the first to receive a CD with a stunning sleeve designed using Francesca's beautiful artwork, signed with all my love, or a digital download if you prefer;
Choose from five exquisite framed prints - illustrated reflections of the songs - by Francesca Booth;

Lyrics and chords to any of my songs for you to learn, with some extra teaching if wanted;
Opportunities to work with me 1-1 or as part of a gathering out in nature to receive personalised healing mantras and sound healing, learn sacred songs, and explore and develop your relationship with your own voice and creativity;
Join me and my new band for a wonderful launch party to celebrate the big day, with a live rendition of the whole album including no less than FOUR part harmonies (anyone who knows me well will know that harmonies are my thing so this is very exciting for me!).
So please see what inspires you! Contributions are a minimum guideline so please give whatever you want. Please get in touch if you want to discuss your own tailor made option. If you want more juice... read on!The Creation StoryCreation features one of my earliest songs, ‘Baba Yaga’, which came to me in the midst of writing my lullabies and was an important sign of things to come. Baba Yaga is a fierce archetype of death and transformation and although in the song I am calling to her, in many ways it has always been her calling to me."Send your plough o'er the bones of the deadAnd let the ground renew the skin that you shed..."Baba Yaga, CreationBaba Yaga called in the death of the 'me' that identified as a sweet gentle soul that didn't want to get things wrong or ruffle anybody up the wrong way. Out of the ashes of Baba Yaga's fire is emerging a woman so committed to speaking her own truth that ruffling feathers becomes inevitable; a woman that no longer wants to apologise for who she is and what she feels; a woman beginning to feel secure enough in her self-worth to follow the call of her heart even if it means being judged; a woman who is beginning to love and accept herself in all her perfect imperfection.I could feel Baba Yaga brewing within me for months, and once finally born into song, I found it utterly terrifying to play for at least two years! It expresses something of my spirit that I hadn't consciously shown to anyone before. However as she began to live through me again, she breathed a new power into my life and my song-writing. In retrospect I see that she needed her own soul family of songs to live amongst.The Songs:
'Baba Yaga' - The album's big mama! 
'Excalibur' - My call for courage... Calling on the divine masculine sword of light to cut through and illuminate anything in my perception that is not truth, and pry away the grasping, clawing fear that I needed to hide my heart's expression to retain the approval of others; 
'Call to Love' arrived when I received my spiritual name from Great Spirit: 'Mbilou', the Eagle. This name is my inner compass that guides me towards my true nature as a leader and visionary; 
'Forge & Flow' celebrates our connection with Gaia and the elements; 
'Open Your Heart' reminds us that EVERYTHING is born out of love, even our most terrible and violent shadows... because love is all there is; 
'I Will Break' was born one sunny day in my garden in a spirit of playful and childlike resilience, reminding us that every time we break we simply dissolve into the sea of love where we reclaim our divine power; 
'Her Calling' reminds us of the spark of life that moves in all things, reclaiming a joyous devotion for the ancient creator Goddess archetype; 
'These Loving Arms', 'I Am', 'Dissolving' and 'Red White & Black' are deep prayers for our collective remembering; 
and 'New Dawn' is my hope filled vision of a future lived in community.
This album has grown out of a journey of deep personal transformation and awakening, through a profoundly life-changing relationship and into the first stage of its excruciating break up. As opposed to the more subtle and maternal reflections of my lullabies, they are songs that answer Baba Yaga's call for the wilder Shakti energies and powerful masculine forces to take their places in my life, and to embrace my path as a role model for living in the heart. The InvitationThese songs are calling us all to wake up, stand together in our power, let go of our shame, and see the hidden shadows at work in our lives, accepting them for their gifts. They invite our gentle compassion and soft intimacy to dance with our fierce independence in the uncompromising light of truth. They remind us that we are perfect, whole and inextricably linked to the great web of life.This album is a fierce cry from the depths of my heart to yours - join me! Let us sing and dance wildly together and surrender ourselves to the eternally renewing energy of Creation.A force with Nature, Ruth deserves a global platform so thatthe rest of the planet can heal through her unique offerings.” (Steve Lee, Glastonbury FM ) With love, hope and lots and lots of gratitude,Ruth x--FYI If I don't reach the full amount, I do still get the money and I will use what I have to get as much done as I can. I trust the album will reach the world when it wants to and not before. X
